description: Lists your Anycast static IP lists.

nested_items.name: AnycastIpLists
nested_items.description: Root level tag for the AnycastIpLists parameters.

nested_items.name: Items
nested_items.description: Items in the Anycast static IP list collection. Each item is of the  AnycastIpListSummary structure type.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The ID of the Anycast static IP list.

nested_items.name: Name
nested_items.description: The name of the Anycast static IP list.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The deployment status of the Anycast static IP list. Valid values: Deployed, Deploying, or Failed.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Anycast static IP list.

nested_items.name: IpCount
nested_items.description: The number of IP addresses in the Anycast static IP list.

nested_items.name: LastModifiedTime
nested_items.description: The last time the Anycast static IP list was modified.

nested_items.name: Marker
nested_items.description: Use this field when paginating results to indicate where to begin in your list. The response includes items in the list that occur after the marker. To get the next page of the list, set this field's value to the value of NextMarker from the current page's response.

nested_items.name: NextMarker
nested_items.description: Indicates the next page of the Anycast static IP list collection. To get the next page of the list, use this value in the Marker field of your request.

nested_items.name: MaxItems
nested_items.description: The maximum number of Anycast static IP list collections that you want returned in the response.

nested_items.name: IsTruncated
nested_items.description: If there are more items in the list collection than are in this response, this value is true.

nested_items.name: Quantity
nested_items.description: The quantity of Anycast static IP lists in the collection.
